## Gateway silently drops duplicate PEER_REQUEST — node stuck in enrollment

### Bug

When a node sends a PEER_REQUEST for a node_id already registered, the gateway returns None (no PEER_ACK). If the original PEER_ACK was lost (e.g. modem ESP-NOW TX failure after BLE pairing — #447), the node retries forever but never completes enrollment.

### Fix

On duplicate PEER_REQUEST, look up the existing node record and compare PSK:
- **Matching PSK**: send PEER_ACK anyway so the node can set eg_complete
- **Different PSK**: silently discard (potential replay/conflict)

### Spec updates (spec-first)

- **GW-1218**: Added criteria 4 (duplicate with matching PSK gets PEER_ACK) and 5 (different PSK discarded)
- **gateway-design.md §17.5**: Updated step 6 and §17.6
- **gateway-validation.md**: Added T-1218a and T-1218b

Fixes #465.
